      "content": "Thanks for the outline. The problem is that we're in a highly constrained environment where running Valgrind or heavy instrumentation isn't really an option—the overhead is too high for our real-time requirements. It's also a bit of a ghost hunt; the leak is so slow and subtle that it's incredibly hard to pin down to a specific module. It just feels like something is quietly eating away at our resources in the background without being obvious.\n\nSince I can't use heavy debuggers, what are some lighter-weight ways to track these \"invisible\" allocations or identify if they're coming from a specific subsystem without crashing the real-time performance?",
